<article class="jsRealFakeNews" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500">
  <div class="activity-box">
    <p>
    20 articles have been downloaded for you to use as training data. Read each image carefully and consider the headline, author (if there is one) and the source. 
    </p>

    <p>
      When you are ready to label the training data, drag and drop the image into the correct Fake News Detector box based on your assessment of whether it is real news or fake news.

    </p>

    <div class="fake-news-detector">
      <div class="fake-news-detector__slide fake-news-detector__slide--1">
        <span class="fake-news-detector__counter"> 1/20 </span>
        <div class="fake-news-detector__article-container">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="fake-news-detector__g-container">
        <div class="fake-news-detector__sign">Fake News Detector</div>
      </div>

      <div class="fake-news-detector__g-container">
        <div class="fake-news-detector__drop fake-news-detector__result">
          <div class="jsReal fake-news-detector__drop-zone">
            <div class="fake-news-detector__drop-zone__target">
              <span> ? </span>
            </div>

            <span class="fake-news-detector__drop-zone__label"> Real News </span>
          </div>

          <div class="jsFake fake-news-detector__drop-zone">
            <div class="fake-news-detector__drop-zone__target">
              <span> ? </span>
            </div>

            <span class="fake-news-detector__drop-zone__label"> Fake News </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="success-box hide">Great work! You have successfully labelled your training data!</p>
  </div>
</article>
